# NSLinguisticTagger

This class helps to extract useful informationÂ aboutÂ the text. For example you can extractÂ lemmas, parts of speech, language of the sentence etc. There are plenty use cases for this technology. I'd speculate that apps like [Fantastical](https://flexibits.com/fantastical) use this technologyÂ to understand user input better.

As a toy example of linguistic tagger, imagine we are building a new hot social network, and we want to process text input, replacing all occurrences of variousÂ verbs with corresponding emojis. Assuming that we are bootstrapped, we can't afford doing it on the server.Â Let's do it client-side!Â SimpleÂ client-side mapping andÂ find and replace should do. Let's say we are searching for "read" to replace it with "ğŸ“š". A prefix search would also match "reading" and most other forms.Â But "to eat" is a little trickier: we might see "ate" and it still should be replaced withÂ ğŸ½.

